        "last_activity_date": 1532722981,
        "creation_date": 1532722981,
        "body": "<p>Since Java 9, JAXB is no longer part of the JDK. <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/43574427/9818506\">This explanation<\/a> written by Andy Guibert and <a href=\"https://blog.codefx.org/java/java-9-migration-guide/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">this migration guide<\/a> should help you to understand the situation.<\/p>\n\n<p>Therefore <em>\"a quick and dirty solution\"<\/em> is to add <code>--add-modules java.xml.bind<\/code> to your compile process.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 51565053,
        "question_id": 51564844
    }],
